Pitch

Emma er midt i tyverne og utilpas i rollen som nybagt mor. Til et for√¶ldrem√∏de i vuggestuen m√• Emma g√∏re op med sig selv hvor langt hun vil g√• for at skjule sine sande f√∏lelser.

items.text:
Posting this for a filmmaker friend.  Contact him (not me) directly.  "I am creating a pitch deck for a pilot I‚Äôve written and I need an actress or model with extensive dramatic training to portray my lead character in costume.

The character: A late teenage (17-20) British girl. Minors may apply but a guardian MUST be present on phone calls and at all times we are working together. You‚Äôll be angry, fearful and even a seductress all while brandishing a long sword and a flintlock pistol as you will be portraying a female pirate! This pirate passed herself as a male so we will need to get creative to portray that aspect as well. I will share some of my writing ahead of time so you can prepare.

The work: I‚Äôll need you to meet me for a costume fitting likely in Chicago‚Äôs Lincoln Park but that is still TBD. The shoot will take place that same day or the next day (in the west suburbs) for at most 1 ‚Äì 1.5 hours (depending on costume changes) for an indoor photo shoot. I did this shoot once before and we were done in an hour.

The pay: $150 for the shoot plus expenses for travel to the costume fitting."

How to apply: Send a few pictures including at least one recent head shot to: 
Email: dshayatovich@gmail.com. Subject line: Secret of the Sea Photoshoot

# **Short Film Casting Call. Actors Wanted: Project Title: (This Is My) Family **

**Genre: Comedy/Dark Comedy **

**Payment: Expenses Paid Only. **

**Roles:** 
* Co Lead: Shaun. Age 35-50. Male
* Co Lead: Marie. Age. 25-35. Female
* Co Lead: Clare. Age 35-50. Female
* Co Lead: Elizabeth. Age 60-75. Female

Where do we want to hire talent from?** (preference, not a must.) **

**West London/Themes Valley Areas**

**Project Description**

A dysfunctional family is forced together for a family event that ends in expected catastrophe. Clare (the overbearing wife), Shaun (the weak husband), Elizabeth (the narcissistic mother) and Marie (the rebellious daughter) will all try to make it through this painful occasion but there's only so much they can all take.

The film will consist of long uninterrupted segments/scenes all shot within one static shot. This gives the film the feeling of a live theatre performance.

 

**Key dates & Locations**

Shooting Dates: **Friday April 10, Saturday April 11, Sunday April 12 and Monday April 13.** 

**Location TBC, Searching For Location in West London/Thames Valley.**

**Other Key Dates:**

Applicants Will Be Invited To Submit A Self-Tape**. Self-Tape Deadline January 29th.**

In Person Auditions/Chemistry Read Session **In February** - In Elephant & Castle, London Waterloo.

Rehearsals Will Take Place **February/March** - In Elephant & Castle, London Waterloo.

**If you have already submitted in the past for this film, please DO NOT submit again.**

In your submission email please:
* Specify the character/characters you are applying for.
* Provide a headshot and any previous performance material. 
* Tell us where you will be traveling from 

**Any emails without this material will not be moved forward.**

**Please Contact: ****[tylerbrownework@gmail.com](mailto:tylerbrownework@gmail.com)**** with your submission email. **

**Character Bios: **

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YgSmK2taUIIYr4zZDLPzGLkNwSasQsPVSb5NZG2midQ/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YgSmK2taUIIYr4zZDLPzGLkNwSasQsPVSb5NZG2midQ/edit?usp=sharing)

**Directors Statement:**

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1l58konA-objavtznHFvNXUofDin2NcyU6Nkj1ury4TI/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1l58konA-objavtznHFvNXUofDin2NcyU6Nkj1ury4TI/edit?usp=sharing)

items.text:
CASTING CALL - small indie film shooting in Colorado Springs on January 30. There are 2 scenes shooting that day. 
1. Coffee Shop: 12 people, portraying patrons, students, etc., dressed in comfortable clothes, 1p-5p.
2. Hospital: 3 people, portraying EMS personnel, dressed in scrubs, 6p-9p.

Rate: IMDB credit, crafty available, footage upon completion

Production Company: Legacy Landmarks Studio, Golden Hour Grid

Title: The Last Frame

Logline: A military veteran finds happiness and purpose after meeting the woman who changes his life - but after a sudden accident and one irreversible mistake, their love collapses into devastating consequences. 

Genre: Drama

Run Time: 10 minutes

Location: Colorado Springs, Colorado

Distribution: YouTube, February 11, 2026

TO SUBMIT: Email [legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com](mailto:legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com) ; Subject: TLF Casting; Include: Headshot, Resume, Reel (if available), Role you are submitting for, Availability for 1/30/2026.

Note: In exchange for offering your services as an actor, our production team would like to offer a 10 second footage compilation of your individual performance on this project for your demo reel. Please submit by January 26, 2026. Thank you!

items.summary:
# **Short Film Casting Call. Actors Wanted: Project Title: (This Is My) Family **

**Genre: Comedy/Dark Comedy **

**Payment: Expenses Paid Only. **

**Roles:** 
* Co Lead: Shaun. Age 35-50. Male
* Co Lead: Marie. Age. 25-35. Female
* Co Lead: Clare. Age 35-50. Female
* Co Lead: Elizabeth. Age 60-75. Female

Where do we want to hire talent from?** (preference, not a must.) **

**West London/Themes Valley Areas**

**Project Description**

A dysfunctional family is forced together for a family event that ends in expected catastrophe. Clare (the overbearing wife), Shaun (the weak husband), Elizabeth (the narcissistic mother) and Marie (the rebellious daughter) will all try to make it through this painful occasion but there's only so much they can all take.

The film will consist of long uninterrupted segments/scenes all shot within one static shot. This gives the film the feeling of a live theatre performance.

 

**Key dates & Locations**

Shooting Dates: **Friday April 10, Saturday April 11, Sunday April 12 and Monday April 13.** 

**Location TBC, Searching For Location in West London/Thames Valley.**

**Other Key Dates:**

Applicants Will Be Invited To Submit A Self-Tape**. Self-Tape Deadline January 29th.**

In Person Auditions/Chemistry Read Session **In February** - In Elephant & Castle, London Waterloo.

Rehearsals Will Take Place **February/March** - In Elephant & Castle, London Waterloo.

**If you have already submitted in the past for this film, please DO NOT submit again.**

In your submission email please:
* Specify the character/characters you are applying for.
* Provide a headshot and any previous performance material. 
* Tell us where you will be traveling from 

**Any emails without this material will not be moved forward.**

**Please Contact: ****[tylerbrownework@gmail.com](mailto:tylerbrownework@gmail.com)**** with your submission email. **

**Character Bios: **

ACTING IN LONG-FORM IMPROV
3-Hour Intensive with Arek Ziƒôtek
Go deeper into story, character, and relationships.
For improvisers with basic experience and curious newcomers ready to play.
This is a focused intensive (not a jam).
We move from core principles to advanced long-form tools, blending acting craft with improvisation to create grounded, honest scenes.
You‚Äôll work on:
‚Ä¢ Building believable characters in the moment
‚Ä¢ Emotional truth & listening
‚Ä¢ Relationships that drive long-form stories
‚Ä¢ Presence, commitment & clarity on stage
‚Ä¢ Sustaining scenes beyond jokes
Acting first. Comedy second. Real, playful, alive.
With Arek Ziƒôtek
Warsaw-based theatre teacher, trained in the Keith Johnstone tradition (Theatresports)
üìÜ Sunday ¬∑ Jan 25
‚è∞ 2:00‚Äì5:00 PM
üìç Po≈Çudnik 2.0 ¬∑ Wilcza 25, Warsaw
üé≠ Limited spots
Strengthen your craft. Deepen your scenes.
Leave with tools you can actually use on stage.

üî• CAST ANNOUNCEMENT FOR NO GENTLE GOODNIGHT üé¨

Sunny Runny Films and Going Nowhere Productions are excited to announce that Luke Dyson will be appearing in our upcoming film No Gentle Goodnight.

Luke is someone whose journey speaks for itself ü•ä. He‚Äôs faced serious adversity in his life, come through it with grit and discipline, and done so while bringing others with him. That resilience and sense of responsibility run through everything he does, both inside and outside the ring.

What stands out most to us is Luke‚Äôs character. He‚Äôs a man of his word, deeply connected to his community, and someone who understands the importance of backing people and ideas he believes in. The fact he‚Äôs chosen to give his time and energy to this project reflects the values he lives by.

Having Luke involved in No Gentle Goodnight means a great deal to us, and we‚Äôre grateful for the trust he‚Äôs shown in what we‚Äôre building. We‚Äôre looking forward to working together and sharing the film with you all üé•

Welcome to the team, Luke ü§ù

üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì ‚ÄòGaffa Cakes‚Äô Short Commercial 

We are casting for a short, character-driven commercial being made as part of our final year on the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Concept: 
Set inside a football changing room, the commercial follows an explosive football manager at breaking point. Built around heightened behaviour and recognisable football culture, the piece uses comedy and character to capture a moment where anger gives way to something unexpected.

Role ‚Äì 
Football Manager (Lead): We‚Äôre looking for a performer to play a stereotypical angry football gaffer ‚Äî loud, intense, and emotionally charged. The role is performance-led, combining dialogue, physicality, and strong character presence. Think Steve Bracknall, with familiar touchline anger and intensity.

Filming: Bristol, w/c 2nd February (exact date TBC)

This is a student production, unpaid, with travel expenses and food provided, and will be used for portfolio and university showcase.

To apply: Please send headshots and CVs to scarlet2.gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Join us at our next ACTOR‚ÄôS SALON happening March 5th from 7-11pm at 1901 Arts Club in London! Attendance is LIMITED for both sharings and audience, so read more below and sign up on our website via the link below! üéâüé≠

[https://www.demidovstudiolondon.com/events/theactorssalonmarch26](https://www.demidovstudiolondon.com/events/theactorssalonmarch26)

Demidov Studio London presents: The Actor‚Äôs Salon

A meeting place for creative artists to share their work, connect with community and celebrate creativity.

Inspired by the great literary and theatrical Salons of the past, where actors, writers and visionaries gathered to share their work in an intimate setting, The Actor‚Äôs Salon is a space for artists to present their work ‚Äì or work in progress ‚Äì in a supportive, non-judgemental setting.

Whether you are an actor wanting to test out a monologue or an audition piece, a scene or a song, a writer wanting to try out an idea with actors, or other creative artist with an urge to bring life to an idea in front of a receptive audience, we have created this space for you.

In true Demidov spirit, it‚Äôs all about process, not result; away from the pressures of auditions, self tapes, rehearsals and the loneliness of one‚Äôs home studio. A place to connect where the artist in us is nurtured and perhaps collaborations are formed.

Come share your work and/or a drink with us!

NEXT SALON
Thursday March 5th from 7pm - 11pm

1901 Arts Club, 7 Exton Street, London SE1 8UE

EVENT INFORMATION

We are delighted to be hosting our next Actor‚Äôs Salon at 1901 Arts Club. The old school master‚Äôs house maintains its late Victorian exterior while the Club‚Äôs beautiful interior re-creates the intimate ambience of a private residence. As such space is LIMITED TO 24 PEOPLE, therefore ATTENDANCE IS BY RSVP BOOKING ONLY. Please note that we won‚Äôt be able to accommodate drop-ins.

There is no entry fee.

Drinks will be available for purchase at this event.

All artists and creatives are welcome!

@1901artsclub 

~
Demidov Studio London
The UK‚Äôs only certified Demidov Acting School
Located at Pushkin House, 5a Bloomsbury Square, London WC1A 2TA
demidovstudiolondon.com
All classes and courses taught by studio Founder & Director @andrei_biziorek

CASTING CALL - ACTORS WANTED (MULTIPLE ROLES)

"Orthodox" We are filming our final year project at Sheffield Hallam University in the Film and TV productions Course.

This is a boxing drama film based around the themes of anti-bullying, abuse and overcoming fear, the film will be focused on the main fight scene being a championship bout between the protagonist and the antagonist.

Shoot Dates will be 9th February - 23rd February. The film will be shot around Sheffield City Centre, actors will need to be in Sheffield or nearby to make the trip for themselves. Travel costs will be covered if necessary. Food and drink will be provided on set, please tell us beforehand if you have any allergies.

Please provide you showreels, portfolio, headshots and any other previous work to araomarfilm12@outlook.com

My university email is c3013899@hallam.shu.ac.uk if this is needed.

üé•CASTING CALL ‚Äî WAR-TIME DRAMA SHORT FILM

We are casting Enemy Soldiers and Civilians for an intense, large-scale Field Hospital sequence in a war-time drama short film.

üìÖ January 24‚Äì25 (primarily Sunday, January 25)
üìç Big Dalton, Glendora

The film follows a teenage girl forced into adulthood while trying to survive in the midst of war. This Field Hospital scene is a major turning point: civilians gather at night believing they are safe, when a sudden enemy attack erupts and everything collapses into chaos.

We are looking for as many people as possible to create a crowded, immersive environment. This is a physically active, emotionally intense scene involving movement, urgency, and controlled chaos.

Details:
 ‚Ä¢ One-day, non-paid role
 ‚Ä¢ Food provided
 ‚Ä¢ Film credit + copy of the film provided
 ‚Ä¢ Seeking White / European actors

If you‚Äôre interested or know someone who might be, please contact tancproduction@gmail.com 

Our film website: https://tancproduction.netlify.app/#support

If you a passionate and organized individual looking to learn how to produce movies, this is your chance to step onto a professional film set and dive into an incredible learning opportunity! We're on the lookout for someone eager to learn, grow, and be mentored by experienced professionals. If you‚Äôre ready to elevate your career and take the next exciting step in filmmaking, we want to hear from you! Availability on Saturdays is a must. Shoot us an email at info@empoweringfilmmakers.org. 

Please note that this position is offered for credit and as a valuable learning experience designed to pave your way to success in the movie industry.

CASTING CALL - small indie film shooting in Colorado Springs on January 30. There are 2 scenes shooting that day. 
1. Coffee Shop: 12 people, portraying patrons, students, etc., dressed in comfortable clothes, 1p-5p.
2. Hospital: 3 people, portraying EMS personnel, dressed in scrubs, 6p-9p.

Rate: IMDB credit, crafty available, footage upon completion

Production Company: Legacy Landmarks Studio, Golden Hour Grid

Title: The Last Frame

Logline: A military veteran finds happiness and purpose after meeting the woman who changes his life - but after a sudden accident and one irreversible mistake, their love collapses into devastating consequences. 

Genre: Drama

Run Time: 10 minutes

Location: Colorado Springs, Colorado

Distribution: YouTube, February 11, 2026

TO SUBMIT: Email [legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com](mailto:legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com) ; Subject: TLF Casting; Include: Headshot, Resume, Reel (if available), Role you are submitting for, Availability for 1/30/2026.

Note: In exchange for offering your services as an actor, our production team would like to offer a 10 second footage compilation of your individual performance on this project for your demo reel. Please submit by January 26, 2026. Thank you!

items.text:
We are now casting our Spring show Shake Rattle And Roll and looking for self Contained experienced hardworking performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community .The
The show is a celebration to all the greatest songs and stars of the 50s 60s 70s The Beatles ,Elvis, Doris Day, Connie Francis ,Cliff Richard, Buddy Holly and more.

Dates

Rehearsals- 23rd -27th February 

Playing Dates- 2nd March-3rd May 

We work Monday to Friday (2 x 60 minute shows per day) 

Casting Breakdown We are now looking for strong /experienced Male and Female singer /performers 

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced performers that can hold an audience and are looking for engaging vocalist performers.

We are looking for drivers with cars only .

We are looking for performers on all area of the UK -please include bases when sending details.

We are offering 700 per week plus fuel on the road 

Please send details including a singing reel to info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

Hi all,

This is the casting call for Metalhead, a short film directed by [Cian Thompson](https://www.facebook.com/groups/187027865191672/user/100000968315007/?__cft__[0]=AZYNpyRx_Gita4pp6dWYoqcY80hQ_oBDclRJC0hhtGwSkei2KmiATstlnhQo4kPOb_R5VGhZYWZDjq9prIWXlXm2s-JXUqoFlhXfgaQCVSXH4GIW7OoDofVkPUdLHIQhonQqp79YBOuCZut5YVXdQKMc&__tn__=-]K-R) a project which he's very passionate about and our hope is that you may be to.

The film is about a punk rocker is forced to put his life back together after an incident in a mosh pit leaves him with a severe cranial injury.

Filming will commence on the 27th & 28th of January in Stoke-on-Trent.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch with Cian at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk or with myself (AD) at guillermoyanezdiz@yahoo.com 

VOLUNTEER ONLY

As of our very limited budget we can only pay for travel expenses and provide catering for cast and crew.

items.summary:
Hi all,

This is the casting call for Metalhead, a short film directed by [Cian Thompson](https://www.facebook.com/groups/187027865191672/user/100000968315007/?__cft__[0]=AZYNpyRx_Gita4pp6dWYoqcY80hQ_oBDclRJC0hhtGwSkei2KmiATstlnhQo4kPOb_R5VGhZYWZDjq9prIWXlXm2s-JXUqoFlhXfgaQCVSXH4GIW7OoDofVkPUdLHIQhonQqp79YBOuCZut5YVXdQKMc&__tn__=-]K-R) a project which he's very passionate about and our hope is that you may be to.

The film is about a punk rocker is forced to put his life back together after an incident in a mosh pit leaves him with a severe cranial injury.

Filming will commence on the 27th & 28th of January in Stoke-on-Trent.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch with Cian at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk or with myself (AD) at guillermoyanezdiz@yahoo.com 

VOLUNTEER ONLY

As of our very limited budget we can only pay for travel expenses and provide catering for cast and crew.

items.title: Hi all,

items.text:
Wanted: 2 actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays.

We are looking for two versatile actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays: ‚ÄúThe Balled of Crooked Lane‚Äù by Tom Mclennan and ‚ÄúWake‚Äù by Day Sheehan, to be performed on Wed 25th February (the awards evening) at the Gladstone Theatre, Port Sunlight. Both play were part of the Liverpool Fringe and won numerous nominations for best play etc.

Plays and parts descriptions.
‚ÄúThe Ballad of Crooked Lane‚Äù is set on the day Edward Rushton, prominent anti-slavery campaigner and blind poet, now well into middle age, awaits eye surgery to regain his sight. While waiting, he goes over his eventful life with his friend and biographer, William Shepherd, the Minister of Gateacre Chapel.

The part: The actor would play Billy the Ballad-monger in one important scene, a lively, upfront character full of humour, a seller of broadside ballads and casual acquaintance of Rushton. The actor would also fulfil several other small roles and be fully active on stage in what is an ensemble production.

‚ÄúWake‚Äù When Daniel Anderson finds himself in an unfamiliar place with fragments of the previous night missing from his memory, he must piece together the truth of what happened. This experimental drama explores themes of guilt, responsibility, and the price of self-deception in a world where nothing is quite what it seems.

The part: POLICE OFFICER 2 (Any gender, 30s+) - The psychological manipulator who probes emotional wounds. The actor needs to be versatile as this role requires them to be multi faceted

No particular age or even gender is necessarily required We are looking for  actors who can bring the characters to life.

Audition date: Monday 26th January 7pm. Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Contact info@valleytheatre.co.uk or turn up on the night. No prep needed. audition will consist of short extract from the script.

Please note: There is no fee for these roles. Hopefully the material and occasion will appeal.

‚ÄúThe Ballad of Crooked Lane‚Äù is set on the day Edward Rushton, prominent anti-slavery campaigner and blind poet, now well into middle age, awaits eye surgery to regain his sight. While waiting, he goes over his eventful life with his friend and biographer, William Shepherd, the Minister of Gateacre Chapel.

The part: The actor would play Billy the Ballad-monger in one important scene, a lively, upfront character full of humour, a seller of broadside ballads and casual acquaintance of Rushton. The actor would also fulfil several other small roles and be fully active on stage in what is an ensemble production.

‚ÄúWake‚Äù When Daniel Anderson finds himself in an unfamiliar place with fragments of the previous night missing from his memory, he must piece together the truth of what happened. This experimental drama explores themes of guilt, responsibility, and the price of self-deception in a world where nothing is quite what it seems.

The part: POLICE OFFICER 2 (Any gender, 30s+) - The psychological manipulator who probes emotional wounds. The actor needs to be versatile as this role requires them to be multi faceted

No particular age or even gender is necessarily required We are looking for  actors who can bring the characters to life.

Audition date: Monday 26th January 7pm. Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Contact info@valleytheatre.co.uk or turn up on the night. No prep needed. audition will consist of short extract from the script.

Please note: There is no fee for these roles. Hopefully the material and occasion will appeal.

# **Short Film Casting Call. Actors Wanted: Project Title: (This Is My) Family **

**Genre: Comedy/Dark Comedy **

**Payment: Expenses Paid Only. **

**Roles:** 
* Co Lead: Shaun. Age 35-50. Male
* Co Lead: Marie. Age. 25-35. Female
* Co Lead: Clare. Age 35-50. Female
* Co Lead: Elizabeth. Age 60-75. Female

Where do we want to hire talent from?** (preference, not a must.) **

**West London/Themes Valley Areas**

**Project Description**

A dysfunctional family is forced together for a family event that ends in expected catastrophe. Clare (the overbearing wife), Shaun (the weak husband), Elizabeth (the narcissistic mother) and Marie (the rebellious daughter) will all try to make it through this painful occasion but there's only so much they can all take.

The film will consist of long uninterrupted segments/scenes all shot within one static shot. This gives the film the feeling of a live theatre performance.

 

**Key dates & Locations**

Shooting Dates: **Friday April 10, Saturday April 11, Sunday April 12 and Monday April 13.** 

**Location TBC, Searching For Location in West London/Thames Valley.**

**Other Key Dates:**

Applicants Will Be Invited To Submit A Self-Tape**. Self-Tape Deadline January 29th.**

In Person Auditions/Chemistry Read Session **In February** - In Elephant & Castle, London Waterloo.

Rehearsals Will Take Place **February/March** - In Elephant & Castle, London Waterloo.

**If you have already submitted in the past for this film, please DO NOT submit again.**

In your submission email please:
* Specify the character/characters you are applying for.
* Provide a headshot and any previous performance material. 
* Tell us where you will be traveling from 

**Any emails without this material will not be moved forward.**

**Please Contact: ****[tylerbrownework@gmail.com](mailto:tylerbrownework@gmail.com)**** with your submission email. **

**Character Bios: **

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YgSmK2taUIIYr4zZDLPzGLkNwSasQsPVSb5NZG2midQ/edit?usp=sharing

**Directors Statement:**

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1l58konA-objavtznHFvNXUofDin2NcyU6Nkj1ury4TI/edit?usp=sharing 

**This Casting Call **

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IsDHX52fXBBgGuZpRE9bIYmzDHfjd-60uFoU1nSo7V8/edit?usp=sharing

Casting call - Stray Dog
Currently casting all roles for 10 minute graduate film based in Bristol and surrounding areas. 

Set in the 1930‚Äôs, Stray Dog follows two silent cinema owning brothers during the rise of the ‚ÄúTalkies‚Äù. Oz leaves his brother and sets up his travelling cinema with lover Nancy. They party and discover how it feels to be free, but grow apart when Oz can‚Äôt learn to be serious. Eventually, a car crash allows Oz to come to terms with who he‚Äôs become and reflect on the important things in life. 

As it‚Äôs a student film, we are seeking contributors on a voluntary basis, but food and travel expenses will be covered. 

Shoot length is a maximum of 5 days, and will take place between end of February and start of March (dates TBC). 

We would love to hear from you! Please email: ttpsfilm@yahoo.com

Comedy short film - 10 minutes 

A struggling theater show is made worse by a new member of the crew who‚Äôs inexperience makes it a night to remember.

Lee (male 20-30)

An ambitious theatre worker who is always wanting more out of life. Can be naive to the ways of the world but has blind optimism that gets him

through stressful times.

A sarcastic, hardworking tech worker who struggles to find joy from his work. Wants to use his talents elsewhere but has no motivation to do so.

The theatre plays stressed out director who struggles with the demand of the actors and lack of backstage crew.

CASTING MULTIPLE PAID ROLES for Season 2 of our show + the upcoming short crime drama ‚ÄúMERIT SOCIETY‚Äù.  Please read character breakdowns and all info below before submitting!!

MERIT SOCIETY

Produced & Directed by Sheilava 
A Callbacks Competition

LOGLINE:

When revelations of the past threaten to sabotage her admission to the Merit Society, a young college student takes action to secure her reputation and become the leader of the most prestigious organization on campus.

SYNOPSIS: 

Zara Boucher, a high-achieving transfer student, sets her sights on joining the elite Merit Society. When a fellow student begins to probe into her dark past, Zara denies the allegations‚Äîuntil the threat of exposure forces her to act.  She murders her sole accuser, erasing the last obstacle to her ascent.  With her past buried and her future secured, Zara is welcomed into the Merit Society, where her ruthless ambition is rewarded as she rises to adulation and power, ultimately elected both President and Secretary.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

ZARA - LEAD (early 20‚Äôs) 

-Female 

-Open to ethnicity

-A junior in college. Zara is ambitious, exploitive and manipulative. She is a super intelligent 5.0 GPA genius and uses her looks to get ahead. She has a grandiose sense of self and entitlement, but a need for admiration masks deep insecurities and lack of empathy for others. She will do anything to get her way. In short, she fits the profile of a narcissistic killer.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

FERNANDO ‚ÄúFERNIE‚Äù (early 20‚Äôs)

-Open to Male / Male Identifying or Non-Binary actors 

-Open to ethnicity

- A senior about to graduate.  ‚ÄúFernie‚Äù is a good looking, straight arrow, genius student who has sacrificed his time and energy by taking on the positions of both President and Secretary of the Merit Society. They has a great personality and will go far in life. They are in control of themself and are amused at Zara‚Äôs efforts to manipulate.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

PROFESSOR HIGGINS (mid 30‚Äôs to early 40‚Äôs)

-Male

-Open to ethnicity

-Prof Higgins is bored with life and uses his position as professor to flirt and take advantage of college coeds. At one point he had dreams to be a published author but they didn‚Äôt pan out and he was forced to teach history to pay the bills. He has been stuck in this rut for over a decade.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

GLEN - (19-23 yrs old)

-Open to Male / Male Identifying or Non-Binary actors 

-Open to ethnicity

-A sophomore in college. Glen is a history nerd who geeks out on tech. They value knowledge and logic over social trends. He has an inflated view of himself and believes he is in control, but in reality is susceptible to being manipulated when Zara strokes his male ego.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

STUDENT - (18-20) ‚Äî DAY PLAYER

-Open to any gender or non-binary actor

-Open to ethnicity

- This character is one of the prospective new members of the Merit Society.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

FT/BG EXTRAS (18-25) 

-Open to any gender or non-binary actors

-Open to ethnicity

-No prior experience necessary.  We need several folks to play prospective college students in a few crucial scenes involving the Merit Society.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

***SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS***

Send us an email with the subject line: 

YOUR NAME + CHARACTER NAME

Include the following in your email:

- headshots 
- a recent/candid photo (selfies are ok)
- resume, reels, IMDb, and/or links to previous work 

Send to:

callbackscompetition@gmail.com

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

DEADLINE TO SUBMIT:  
Tuesday, January 27th, 5:00pm 

*NOTE: 

This is a non-union, independent production filming in the Greater Austin Area.

Talent will receive meals, IDMb credit, and a paid daily rate (potentially negotiable based on experience). 

ALL TALENT MUST BE BASED IN AUSTIN ‚Äî this is an Austin-based acting competition.  No lodging, transportation, or travel compensation will provided.

A few of our actors will also be selected to appear in Season 2 of our Youtube TV show competition consisting of 3 rounds of a recorded audition process (they will also be paid for each day of filming for this).  The winner of Callbacks Season 2 will receive a cash prize in addition to booking the paid lead role in our upcoming short MERIT SOCIETY. 

Talent must be fully available February 8, February 20-22, and February 26-27 to be considered.

**Good Morning! I am producing a short film in Duluth, GA and we need some PAs and Extras!**

The dates are:

Friday, January 30th

Saturday, January 31st

Sunday, February 1st

On Friday, we are shooting a football sequence, so we primarily need background actors for that day.  (If you have cleats, bring them)

Saturday, we primarily need extras for a classroom scene. (bring any white-collared shirt and khakis)

FInally, on Sunday, we need background actors to play teachers (think cardigans, sweater vests, etc)

Also keep in mind it will be COLD, so dress warm.

If interested, DM me, or email [JackReEnacts@yahoo.com](mailto:JackReEnacts@yahoo.com) for details.

items.text:
Please email us 
Subject: SITCOM
https://www.ancagency.co.uk/submissions

BE BASED IN THE UK/EU/US (must be British!)
MUST BE ON SPOTLIGHT.

Please Do NOT email if you do not have O1/Green Cards 

#castingcall #pilotseason

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'CASTING CALL ANC Acting Now Creatives SITCOM PILOT SHOT IN LOS ANGELES. Seeking British COMEDY actors with 01 VISAS or GREEN CARDS Can be based in the UK or EU. ANC is a talent agency, and we are seeking comedy talent to represent (we are not casting!). Please contact us via our website.'

topComments.text: Wait, what? It clearly says its a casting for a sitcom pilot. Then you say you're not casting. Make your minds up.

sharedPost.text:
Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

**Marketing Interns: Your Next Big Opportunity is Here! üöÄ**

**Kandid Media** is urgently seeking dynamic and driven **Marketing Interns** to join our fast-paced team for a 60-day intensive program.

This isn't just about fetching coffee‚Äîit's about diving headfirst into real-world media strategy, content creation, and campaign execution. If you're ready to learn, innovate, and make a tangible impact, this is your shot.

**The Pathway:** We believe in rewarding talent and hard work. After a successful 60-day internship, top performers will be invited to transition into a **paid part-time position** with Kandid Media. This is your chance to turn passion into profession.

**We're looking for individuals who are:**
* Eager to learn about media, content strategy, and digital marketing.
* Proactive, creative, and reliable.
* Ready to contribute to a growing media company.

**Why Join Kandid Media?** You'll work alongside experienced professionals, gain invaluable hands-on experience, and contribute to projects that span film, branded content, and community-driven initiatives. This is about building your resume with real results and securing your future in the industry.

**Apply Now: Send us a DM with a brief overview of your marketing interest/experience and what social platforms you have the greatest knowledge in. **

We're moving fast, so don't delay!

items.text:
A huge thank you to Apec taxis and MDB Gas ltd for proudly sponsoring us here at Sunny Runny Productions.
Your support means the world to us and plays a massive role in helping us do what we love. We‚Äôre incredibly grateful to partner with local businesses who believe in creativity, community, and growth. üôå
Please show them some love and support the companies that support us!

sharedPost.text:
We‚Äôre incredibly proud and genuinely buzzing to officially welcome Apec Taxis New and MDB GAS Ltd Ltd as our new main sponsors for Sunny Runny Productions.

To have two respected local businesses believe in what we‚Äôre building truly means the world to us. Their support isn‚Äôt just about backing a film or a podcast. It‚Äôs about backing people, ideas, creativity and the belief that when a town pulls together, amazing things can happen.

APEC Taxis have long been part of the fabric of Halton. Always reliable, always visible and always giving back. Whether it‚Äôs supporting local initiatives, helping people get where they need to be, or quietly backing community causes, they show time and time again that they genuinely care about the area and the people in it.

MDB Gas Ltd represent everything good about local business. Professional, trusted, hardworking and community-minded. They look after homes and businesses across Runcorn and beyond, and they do it with pride, integrity and a real sense of responsibility. They support people not just when it‚Äôs convenient, but when it matters.

A huge heartfelt thank you to Mike Holland and Dean Kenno at APEC and to Dean Burge and Lisa Burge at MDB Gas. Thank you for believing in us, for backing No Gentle Goodnight, for supporting The Sunny Runny Podcast Show, and for standing alongside a group of creatives who want to tell honest stories, make people laugh and do something positive for our town.

This partnership is about more than sponsorship. It‚Äôs about shared values, shared pride and a shared belief that Runcorn deserves investment, creativity, laughter and hope.

Now let‚Äôs go make a movie. Let‚Äôs put the world to rights on the podcast. And let‚Äôs bring some sparkle, fun and a bit of glorious chaos back into the town with our sketches and shenanigans.

#SunnyRunnyProductions #NoGentleGoodnight #SunnyRunnyPodcast #Runcorn #Halton #CommunityFirst #LocalBusiness #SupportLocal

items.text:
Casting for leading Man/Leading Lady young adult early to mid-20's.
I'm shooting another short vertical demo for two days between now and February 8 (dates TBA) and am looking for two non-union actors with comedic acting chops, to play out the dialogue in this romantic comedy (a few scenes).

Shooting will be in downtown and East Vancouver, there will be a rehearsal day after actors are off-book and then we shoot.

This is a demo, voluntary, for actors reel and directing sample.

If interested, please email me your photo, resume and availability to castingproject604@gmail.com.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL - Non-union **

Looking for Slavic/Eastern European looking actors for small, non-speaking roles in short film, During Winter, I Thought of My Father, a Russian language short film by Daniil Vasilyev. 

**ACTORS DO NOT NEED TO SPEAK RUSSIAN AS THE ROLES ARE NON-SPEAKING. **

**Main Shoot Dates: Feb 14th-16th, 2026 **

**Descriptions: **

**Young Russian Man, early 20s: **Need him available for a day in the week leading up to Feb 14th for a photoshoot. 
Specific date TBD, but we are flexible and willing to work with actor's schedule. 

**Older Russian Woman, 50s-60s: **Needed for photoshoot Feb 16th. 

**Older Russian Man, 40s-60s: **Needed for filming Feb 14th, 15th, photoshoot on the 16th. Non-speaking role, will be playing main character's father. 

**Compensation: **IMDb credit, post-film credit, food provided as well as transport if required**. **

**Location: **Greater Vancouver Area 

**If interested, please send an email to ****duringwinter26@gmail.com ****with any headshots or good pictures of yourself, your reel (if you have one), and stats (height, eye colour, etc). **

** **

items.text:
Suche f√ºr ein Musikvideo noch eine Mitspielerin.
 
Gedreht wird zu einem etwas rockigeren Song der gut auf die breite Masse passt. 
Thema ist ‚ÄúLippenstift‚Äù Hei√üt - Du bist die sch√∂nste und darfst dich sch√∂n aufbrezeln. 
Ich Idiot stehe daneben und trage deine T√ºten und gebe dir immer eine bestfriend Meinung. 
 
Im Laufe des Songs ziehe ich das ganze aber mehr und mehr ins l√§cherliche und bring dich zum verzweifeln. 
 
Gedreht werden soll das ganze in einem Supermarkt/Drogerie einem Club oder √§hnlichen und einem Modehaus 
( Szenen beim einkaufen und nat√ºrlich vor dem Lippenstift Regal und vor dem Club ) 
Das Video soll etwas ironisch und spa√üig gestaltet werden, Konfetti schie√üen, Feenstaub werfen etc. Am Ende darfst du mir sogar zeigen wie ich selber fachlich Lippenstift auftrage. 
 
Du musst kein Profi sein 
bestenfalls im Alter von 18 ‚Äì 26 
jugendlicher Stil , schlank und am besten blond oder braunhaarig. 
 
Du solltest arrogant und eingebildet schauen k√∂nnen und etwas gestikulieren. 
Viel mehr ist nicht n√∂tig. 
Und dir das nat√ºrlich zutrauen zu drehen auch wenn es Zuschauer gibt. 
 
Drehort: L√ºneburger Umkreis 
Datum folgt wenn die Locations zugesagt haben. 
Vorweg kann nat√ºrlich ein pers√∂nliches treffen stattfinden um alles durchzukaspern. 
 
Als Dankesch√∂n bekommst du einen Gutschein deiner Wahl im Wert von 50‚Ç¨ ein Fotoshooting f√ºrs Coverbild des Songs und den gekauften Lippenstift hahahah. 
Alle entstandenen Aufnahmen/Bilder darfst du nat√ºrlich auch f√ºr eigene Zwecke verwenden.

Auf Wunsch kann ich dir auch schon ein paar Songausschnitte zeigen :)

items.text:
üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äî VIDEO SUBMISSION REQUIRED

We‚Äôre casting 10 actors for a 1-minute product promo video and are looking for bilingual talent.

üìç Location: DTLA (studio)
üí∞ Pay: $600
üìÖ Shoot Date: Feb 3 (up to 5 hrs, ~2 hrs expected)
üëï Wardrobe Fitting: Jan 30 (30 min)
üì∫ Usage: Internet + events (copyright buyout)

üé≠ WHO WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR

‚úîÔ∏è Any gender
‚úîÔ∏è Ages 14‚Äì90
‚úîÔ∏è Fluent in English + ONE of the following languages:
Spanish, French, German, Japanese, Portuguese, Italian, Dutch, Hindi, Russian

üé• AUDITION REQUIREMENT (MANDATORY)

Please submit a self-tape video of you reading the script below in English AND in your second language.

‚ö†Ô∏è Incomplete submissions will not be considered.

Script (must be read in full, twice):

‚ÄúI get nervous every time I speak, especially when I can‚Äôt see the person on the other end. Without faces or gestures, words have to carry more weight‚Äîand sometimes they fall short. I‚Äôm working every day to bridge that gap. What I hope for isn‚Äôt special treatment; I just hope one day I can be understood for my ideas, for my thinking, and not my accent or where I come from. And I hope that day is today.‚Äù

üì© HOW TO SUBMIT

Email your video self-tape to:
üìß casting@verkada.com

Please include:

Name

Age

Languages spoken

Confirmation of availability for Jan 30 & Feb 3

üé¨ We‚Äôre casting 10 actors ‚Äî excited to see your tapes!

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äî VIDEO SUBMISSION REQUIRED

We‚Äôre casting 10 actors for a 1-minute product promo video and are looking for bilingual talent.

üìç Location: DTLA (studio)
üí∞ Pay: $600
üìÖ Shoot Date: Feb 3 (up to 5 hrs, ~2 hrs expected)
üëï Wardrobe Fitting: Jan 30 (30 min)
üì∫ Usage: Internet + events (copyright buyout)

üé≠ WHO WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR

‚úîÔ∏è Any gender
‚úîÔ∏è Ages 14‚Äì90
‚úîÔ∏è Fluent in English + ONE of the following languages:
Spanish, French, German, Japanese, Portuguese, Italian, Dutch, Hindi, Russian

üé• AUDITION REQUIREMENT (MANDATORY)

Please submit a self-tape video of you reading the script below in English AND in your second language.

‚ö†Ô∏è Incomplete submissions will not be considered.

Script (must be read in full, twice):

‚ÄúI get nervous every time I speak, especially when I can‚Äôt see the person on the other end. Without faces or gestures, words have to carry more weight‚Äîand sometimes they fall short. I‚Äôm working every day to bridge that gap. What I hope for isn‚Äôt special treatment; I just hope one day I can be understood for my ideas, for my thinking, and not my accent or where I come from. And I hope that day is today.‚Äù

üì© HOW TO SUBMIT

Email your video self-tape to:
üìß casting@verkada.com

Please include:

Name

Age

Languages spoken

Confirmation of availability for Jan 30 & Feb 3

üé¨ We‚Äôre casting 10 actors ‚Äî excited to see your tapes!

üé¨ **CALLING CAMERA OPS & SCRIPT SUPERVISORS (LA)**

*3-Day Short Film | Skill Exchange Opportunity*

****1ST COME 1ST SERVE ****

We‚Äôre currently crewing up for a **3-day short film production** and are looking to connect with a few aligned creatives who want to collaborate, build, and create something meaningful together.

**Positions we‚Äôre seeking:**

‚Ä¢ Camera Operator familiar with **Sony & Blackmagic** systems

‚Ä¢ **Script Supervisor**

This project is **unpaid**, but  we‚Äôre offering a **creative exchange** for those who are interested.

‚ú® **What you receive:**

If you have a **concept, visual, or short idea (up to 10 minutes)** you‚Äôve been wanting to bring to life, you‚Äôll receive **full production support** from our collective on your piece (crew, structure, guidance, execution) in exchange for your support on this film.

This is ideal for creatives who:

‚Ä¢ Want real on-set experience with an intentional team

‚Ä¢ Have a short visual idea they‚Äôve been sitting on

‚Ä¢ Value collaboration over transactional gigs

‚Ä¢ Are interested in long-term creative relationships

üìç **Location:** Los Angeles

üìÜ **Shoot:** 3 days (dates shared upon connection)

If this resonates, comment below or DM with:

1. Your role (Cam Op or Script Supervisor)
2. Gear familiarity (if applicable)
3. A brief note on the visual you‚Äôd want support on

CASTING CALL - small indie film shooting in Colorado Springs on January 30. There are 2 scenes shooting that day. 
1. Coffee Shop: 12 people, portraying patrons, students, etc., dressed in comfortable clothes, 1p-5p.
2. Hospital: 3 people, portraying EMS personnel, dressed in scrubs, 6p-9p.

Rate: IMDB credit, crafty available, footage upon completion

Production Company: Legacy Landmarks Studio, Golden Hour Grid

Title: The Last Frame

Logline: A military veteran finds happiness and purpose after meeting the woman who changes his life - but after a sudden accident and one irreversible mistake, their love collapses into devastating consequences. 

Genre: Drama

Run Time: 10 minutes

Location: Colorado Springs, Colorado

Distribution: YouTube, February 11, 2026

TO SUBMIT: Email [legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com](mailto:legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com) ; Subject: TLF Casting; Include: Headshot, Resume, Reel (if available), Role you are submitting for, Availability for 1/30/2026.

Note: In exchange for offering your services as an actor, our production team would like to offer a 10 second footage compilation of your individual performance on this project for your demo reel. Please submit by January 26, 2026. Thank you!

CASTING CALL - Short Dark Comedy/Noir
‚Ä¢ Title: "Murder, No Rush"

‚Ä¢ Type: Short

‚Ä¢ Location: Boulder, CO, Denver, CO

‚Ä¢ Compensation: $25/day (negotiable), lunch provided

‚Ä¢ Shooting Dates: Sunday, January 25th & Sunday, February 1st

SYNOPSIS

Vivian, a vain housewife, conspires to kill her wealthy husband, Benny, by hiring a hitman- but unbeknownst to her, the cops know exactly what she's up to.

ROLES:

‚Ä¢ Benny D'Angelo: Male, 23-35
Vivian's husband. A well-off businessman who fell in love easily, only to now find that his wife might have married him just for the money.

‚Ä¢ Officer K: Male, 30+
A no-nonsense cop with a keen attention to detail. He arrives on the scene of an apparent drug bust, only to discover there may be something much more sinister at hand.
(Only needed on 1/25)

TO SUBMIT:

‚Ä¢ A headshot OR previous work OR request sides, record an audition (please submit by Friday, January 23)

‚Ä¢ Subject Line: "[Your Name] - Murder, No Rush"

If you're interested, please feel free to DM me directly here or email AydanMetsch@gmail.com. Script available upon request!

Gedreht wird zu einem etwas rockigeren Song der gut auf die breite Masse passt. 
Thema ist ‚ÄúLippenstift‚Äù Hei√üt - Du bist die sch√∂nste und darfst dich sch√∂n aufbrezeln. 
Ich Idiot stehe daneben und trage deine T√ºten und gebe dir immer eine bestfriend Meinung. 
 
Im Laufe des Songs ziehe ich das ganze aber mehr und mehr ins l√§cherliche und bring dich zum verzweifeln. 
 
Gedreht werden soll das ganze in einem Supermarkt/Drogerie einem Club oder √§hnlichen und einem Modehaus 
( Szenen beim einkaufen und nat√ºrlich vor dem Lippenstift Regal und vor dem Club ) 
Das Video soll etwas ironisch und spa√üig gestaltet werden, Konfetti schie√üen, Feenstaub werfen etc. Am Ende darfst du mir sogar zeigen wie ich selber fachlich Lippenstift auftrage. 
 
Du musst kein Profi sein 
bestenfalls im Alter von 18 ‚Äì 26 
jugendlicher Stil , schlank und am besten blond oder braunhaarig. 
 
Du solltest arrogant und eingebildet schauen k√∂nnen und etwas gestikulieren. 
Viel mehr ist nicht n√∂tig. 
Und dir das nat√ºrlich zutrauen zu drehen auch wenn es Zuschauer gibt. 
 
Drehort: L√ºneburger Umkreis 
Datum folgt wenn die Locations zugesagt haben. 
Vorweg kann nat√ºrlich ein pers√∂nliches treffen stattfinden um alles durchzukaspern. 
 
Als Dankesch√∂n bekommst du einen Gutschein deiner Wahl im Wert von 50‚Ç¨ ein Fotoshooting f√ºrs Coverbild des Songs und den gekauften Lippenstift hahahah. 
Alle entstandenen Aufnahmen/Bilder darfst du nat√ºrlich auch f√ºr eigene Zwecke verwenden.

Emma er midt i tyverne og utilpas i rollen som nybagt mor. Til et for√¶ldrem√∏de i vuggestuen m√• Emma g√∏re op med sig selv hvor langt hun vil g√• for at skjule sine sande f√∏lelser.
